verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Command the children of Israel, that they put out of the camp every leper, and every one that hath an issue, and whosoever is defiled by the dead:
verses.verse_html: 2Command the children of Israel, that they put out of the camp every leper, and every one that hath an issue, and whosoever is defiled by the dead:

tokens.text: and every one that hath an issue

verses.text_plain: Both male and female shall ye put out, without the camp shall ye put them; that they defile not their camps, in the midst whereof I dwell.
verses.verse_html: 3Both male and female shall ye put out, without the camp shall ye put them; that they defile not their camps, in the midst whereof I dwell.

verses.text_plain: And the children of Israel did so, and put them out without the camp: as the Lord spake unto Moses, so did the children of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 4And the children of Israel did so, and put them out without the camp: as the Lord spake unto Moses, so did the children of Israel.

verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 5And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Speak unto the children of Israel, When a man or woman shall commit any sin that men commit, to do a trespass against the Lord, and that person be guilty;
verses.verse_html: 6Speak unto the children of Israel, When a man or woman shall commit any sin that men commit, to do a trespass against the Lord, and that person be guilty;

verses.text_plain: Then they shall confess their sin which they have done: and he shall recompense his trespass with the principal thereof, and add unto it the fifth part thereof, and give it unto him against whom he hath trespassed.
verses.verse_html: 7Then they shall confess their sin which they have done: and he shall recompense his trespass with the principal thereof, and add unto it the fifth part thereof, and give it unto him against whom he hath trespassed.

verses.text_plain: But if the man have no kinsman to recompense the trespass unto, let the trespass be recompensed unto the Lord, even to the priest; beside the ram of the atonement, whereby an atonement shall be made for him.
verses.verse_html: 8But if the man have no kinsman to recompense the trespass unto, let the trespass be recompensed unto the Lord, even to the priest; beside the ram of the atonement, whereby an atonement shall be made for him.

tokens.text: whereby an atonement shall be made

verses.text_plain: And every offering of all the holy things of the children of Israel, which they bring unto the priest, shall be his.
verses.verse_html:
9And every offering of all the holy things of the children of Israel, which they bring unto the priest, shall be his.
 offering: or, heave offering

footnotes.body_html: offering: or, heave offering

verses.text_plain: And every mans hallowed things shall be his: whatsoever any man giveth the priest, it shall be his.
verses.verse_html: 10And every mans hallowed things shall be his: whatsoever any man giveth the priest, it shall be his.

tokens.text: shall be his: whatsoever any man

verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 11And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, If any mans wife go aside, and commit a trespass against him,
verses.verse_html: 12Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, If any mans wife go aside, and commit a trespass against him,

verses.text_plain: And a man lie with her carnally, and it be hid from the eyes of her husband, and be kept close, and she be defiled, and there be no witness against her, neither she be taken with the manner;
verses.verse_html: 13And a man lie with her carnally, and it be hid from the eyes of her husband, and be kept close, and she be defiled, and there be no witness against her, neither she be taken with the manner;

tokens.text: against her, neither she be taken

verses.text_plain: And the spirit of jealousy come upon him, and he be jealous of his wife, and she be defiled: or if the spirit of jealousy come upon him, and he be jealous of his wife, and she be not defiled:
verses.verse_html: 14And the spirit of jealousy come upon him, and he be jealous of his wife, and she be defiled: or if the spirit of jealousy come upon him, and he be jealous of his wife, and she be not defiled:

tokens.text: upon him, and he be jealous
upon him, and he be jealous

verses.text_plain: Then shall the man bring his wife unto the priest, and he shall bring her offering for her, the tenth part of an ephah of barley meal; he shall pour no oil upon it, nor put frankincense thereon; for it is an offering of jealousy, an offering of memorial, bringing iniquity to remembrance.
verses.verse_html: 15Then shall the man bring his wife unto the priest, and he shall bring her offering for her, the tenth part of an ephah of barley meal; he shall pour no oil upon it, nor put frankincense thereon; for it is an offering of jealousy, an offering of memorial, bringing iniquity to remembrance.

verses.text_plain: And the priest shall bring her near, and set her before the Lord:
verses.verse_html: 16And the priest shall bring her near, and set her before the Lord:

verses.text_plain: And the priest shall take holy water in an earthen vessel; and of the dust that is in the floor of the tabernacle the priest shall take, and put it into the water:
verses.verse_html: 17And the priest shall take holy water in an earthen vessel; and of the dust that is in the floor of the tabernacle the priest shall take, and put it into the water:

verses.text_plain: And the priest shall set the woman before the Lord, and uncover the womans head, and put the offering of memorial in her hands, which is the jealousy offering: and the priest shall have in his hand the bitter water that causeth the curse:
verses.verse_html: 18And the priest shall set the woman before the Lord, and uncover the womans head, and put the offering of memorial in her hands, which is the jealousy offering: and the priest shall have in his hand the bitter water that causeth the curse:

verses.text_plain: And the priest shall charge her by an oath, and say unto the woman, If no man have lain with thee, and if thou hast not gone aside to uncleanness with another instead of thy husband, be thou free from this bitter water that causeth the curse:
verses.verse_html:
19And the priest shall charge her by an oath, and say unto the woman, If no man have lain with thee, and if thou hast not gone aside to uncleanness with another instead of thy husband, be thou free from this bitter water that causeth the curse:
 with another: or, being in the power of thy husband: Heb. under thy husband

tokens.text: shall charge her by an oath
with thee, and if thou hast not gone aside

footnotes.body_text: with another: or, being in the power of thy husband: Heb. under thy husband
footnotes.body_html: with another: or, being in the power of thy husband: Heb. under thy husband

verses.text_plain: But if thou hast gone aside to another instead of thy husband, and if thou be defiled, and some man have lain with thee beside thine husband:
verses.verse_html: 20But if thou hast gone aside to another instead of thy husband, and if thou be defiled, and some man have lain with thee beside thine husband:

tokens.text: But if thou hast gone aside

verses.text_plain: Then the priest shall charge the woman with an oath of cursing, and the priest shall say unto the woman, The Lord make thee a curse and an oath among thy people, when the Lord doth make thy thigh to rot, and thy belly to swell;
verses.verse_html:
21Then the priest shall charge the woman with an oath of cursing, and the priest shall say unto the woman, The Lord make thee a curse and an oath among thy people, when the Lord doth make thy thigh to rot, and thy belly to swell;
 rot: Heb. fall

verses.text_plain: And this water that causeth the curse shall go into thy bowels, to make thy belly to swell, and thy thigh to rot: And the woman shall say, Amen, amen.
verses.verse_html: 22And this water that causeth the curse shall go into thy bowels, to make thy belly to swell, and thy thigh to rot: And the woman shall say, Amen, amen.

verses.text_plain: And the priest shall write these curses in a book, and he shall blot them out with the bitter water:
verses.verse_html: 23And the priest shall write these curses in a book, and he shall blot them out with the bitter water:

verses.text_plain: And he shall cause the woman to drink the bitter water that causeth the curse: and the water that causeth the curse shall enter into her, and become bitter.
verses.verse_html: 24And he shall cause the woman to drink the bitter water that causeth the curse: and the water that causeth the curse shall enter into her, and become bitter.

tokens.text: And he shall cause the woman

verses.text_plain: Then the priest shall take the jealousy offering out of the womans hand, and shall wave the offering before the Lord, and offer it upon the altar:
verses.verse_html: 25Then the priest shall take the jealousy offering out of the womans hand, and shall wave the offering before the Lord, and offer it upon the altar:

verses.text_plain: And the priest shall take an handful of the offering, even the memorial thereof, and burn it upon the altar, and afterward shall cause the woman to drink the water.
verses.verse_html: 26And the priest shall take an handful of the offering, even the memorial thereof, and burn it upon the altar, and afterward shall cause the woman to drink the water.

verses.text_plain: And when he hath made her to drink the water, then it shall come to pass, that, if she be defiled, and have done trespass against her husband, that the water that causeth the curse shall enter into her, and become bitter, and her belly shall swell, and her thigh shall rot: and the woman shall be a curse among her people.
verses.verse_html: 27And when he hath made her to drink the water, then it shall come to pass, that, if she be defiled, and have done trespass against her husband, that the water that causeth the curse shall enter into her, and become bitter, and her belly shall swell, and her thigh shall rot: and the woman shall be a curse among her people.

tokens.text: And when he hath made her to drink

verses.text_plain: And if the woman be not defiled, but be clean; then she shall be free, and shall conceive seed.
verses.verse_html: 28And if the woman be not defiled, but be clean; then she shall be free, and shall conceive seed.

verses.text_plain: This is the law of jealousies, when a wife goeth aside to another instead of her husband, and is defiled;
verses.verse_html: 29This is the law of jealousies, when a wife goeth aside to another instead of her husband, and is defiled;

verses.text_plain: Or when the spirit of jealousy cometh upon him, and he be jealous over his wife, and shall set the woman before the Lord, and the priest shall execute upon her all this law.
verses.verse_html: 30Or when the spirit of jealousy cometh upon him, and he be jealous over his wife, and shall set the woman before the Lord, and the priest shall execute upon her all this law.

verses.text_plain: Then shall the man be guiltless from iniquity, and this woman shall bear her iniquity.
verses.verse_html: 31Then shall the man be guiltless from iniquity, and this woman shall bear her iniquity.
